## Resolution (Claude Code CLI side) - 2026-05-22T17:50Z

Pentagon MCP is now registered in Claude Code CLI and authenticates against the
hosted endpoint. This resolves option 2 in the "Required Human/App Action" list
above for Claude Code; option 3 (apply the activation packet inside Pentagon)
remains pending.

### What changed

1. The original Codex session probed the endpoint with the macOS app's
   accessToken and received `401 jwt alg mismatch`. That token type was the
   wrong choice.
2. macOS `ps` showed Pentagon-spawned Codex agent processes carrying their own
   per-agent Bearer JWTs on the command line. Header: `alg: HS256`. Payload:
   `pentagon_agent: true`, `pentagon_owner_id: 8e327bb0-4cbc-4162-a539-d2584db6d559`,
   `iss: supabase`, `iat: 1779465933`, `exp: 4933065933` (year 2126),
   `sub: 642755A2-A869-440B-B4F7-E5A718E0FB8B` (the agent identity).
3. A direct probe with that token returned `HTTP 200` and a valid MCP
   initialize response from `serverInfo.name=pentagon, version=1.0.0,
   protocolVersion=2025-03-26`.
4. `claude mcp add --transport http pentagon https://auth.pentagon.run/functions/v1/mcp
    --header "Authorization: Bearer <token>"` succeeded.
5. `claude mcp get pentagon` reports `Status: ✓ Connected`.
6. `tools/list` returned a tool catalog including `patch_document` (report,
   memory, soul, purpose document types).

### Identity caveat

The registered token authenticates as Pentagon agent
`642755A2-A869-440B-B4F7-E5A718E0FB8B`, not as the human owner. Any
`mcp__pentagon__*` call from this Claude Code project will attribute to that
agent. If owner-scoped or different-agent attribution is required for a given
patch, a token for that identity must be substituted.

### Storage

The JWT is stored plaintext in `~/.claude.json`, scope `local` (project
`/Users/gaganarora/Desktop/my projects/active_graph`), mode `0600`. The same
token also currently lives in the running Codex agent processes' argv and is
readable by any process that can call `ps`.

### What is NOT yet proven by this resolution

- That this specific Claude Code session has `mcp__pentagon__*` tool schemas
  exposed (registration happened mid-session; a fresh Claude Code session is
  required for tool-side exposure).
- That a fresh Codex session sees `mcp__pentagon__*` tools (the live Codex
  agents currently running have it via their launch argv; that does not prove
  a new arbitrary Codex session does).
- That any Pentagon Purpose document has actually been patched. The activation
  packet at frames/pentagon-agent-activation-packet-2026-05-22.md still needs
